le=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px; border: 0px; max-width: 100%; display: block; width: 742px; height: auto;\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/flrSTN8W2Tj165wC9pSbYWfSpO8=/0x0:742x494/1200x0/filters:focal(0x0:742x494):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/16336638/p4zoom.jpg\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw\" srcset=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/jOgNSVGxaHMRcg6JJz_KfWjNKOI=/0x0:742x494/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:742x494):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/16336638/p4zoom.jpg 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/VNpGDBH0kbiDLkGQ7dvsx-bLflg=/0x0:742x494/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:742x494):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/16336638/p4zoom.jpg 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/LAAo6xXte4Tos_um15itYW99zNc=/0x0:742x494/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:742x494):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/16336638/p4zoom.jpg 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/8mLZ0nTYXB6y3Wvg2b9YXQprDcI=/0x0:742x494/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:742x494):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/16336638/p4zoom.jpg 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/o_AoHPe3gfzCIuOh4yGMApwe-tg=/0x0:742x494/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:742x494):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/16336638/p4zoom.jpg 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/wJIumD2l3FKvyuewfHY9y7bx0pE=/0x0:742x494/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:742x494):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/16336638/p4zoom.jpg 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/aPGQPOATTeQYXPzs71ddE0HSrNU=/0x0:742x494/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:742x494):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/16336638/p4zoom.jpg 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/UlSHuMrZVUQ5oV4drFVQzqQt9gM=/0x0:742x494/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:742x494):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/16336638/p4zoom.jpg 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/TrY7phRZAapqZzyAsau-4csoOL8=/0x0:742x494/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:742x494):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/16336638/p4zoom.jpg 1920w\" alt=\"\" data-upload-width=\"742\" /></picture></span></span>\r\n<figcaption style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; display: inline;\">A brightened version of Google&rsquo;s teaser image.</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<h3 id=\"MevMRl\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: Heroic, \'Arial Narrow\', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: calc(1.5625em); line-height: 1.2; margin: 0px 0px 0.6rem; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; text-transform: uppercase; color: #424242; background-color: #ffffff;\">A MYSTERIOUS THIRD SENSOR</h3>\r\n<p id=\"KJuDx8\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 1.2rem; padding: 0px; color: #424242; background-color: #ffffff;\">Above the two camera lenses is a smaller third&nbsp;<em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">something</em>. You can just barely make out that something is there in the photo Google posted, but if you brighten the image a little, it&rsquo;s clear that there&rsquo;s a cutout.</p>\r\n<p id=\"oPLmCx\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 1.2rem; padding: 0px; color: #424242; background-color: #ffffff;\">What&rsquo;s completely unclear is what that extra sensor might be.</p>\r\n<p id=\"oTHNp7\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 1.2rem; padding: 0px; color: #424242; background-color: #ffffff;\">Last night,&nbsp;<em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Unbox Therapy&nbsp;</em>correctly reported that the Pixel 4&rsquo;s camera bump would have a sensor above the two cameras, which the show&rsquo;s host, Lewis Hilsenteger, identified as a &ldquo;spectral sensor.&rdquo; It&rsquo;s entirely possible that&rsquo;s what we&rsquo;re looking at: the Pixel 3 already has a spectral sensor &mdash; Google also calls it a &ldquo;flicker sensor,&rdquo; and it&rsquo;s used to help the camera deal with strobing lights or screens.</p>\r\n<p id=\"mLtiL5\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 1.2rem; padding: 0px; color: #424242; background-color: #ffffff;\">But the spectral sensor on the Pixel 3 looks a little bit smaller than this. It&rsquo;s possible that sensor is getting an upgrade (spectral sensors can be used to analyze everything from color to&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; background-color: transparent; color: #e5127d; transition: color 0.1s ease 0s, background-color 0.1s ease 0s, fill 0.1s ease 0s; border-bottom: 1px solid currentcolor;\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y6ccmh24BXw\">the makeup of food</a>, though neither of those things have been done inside a phone before). It&rsquo;s also possible that I&rsquo;m wrong, it&rsquo;s the exact same size as before and doing the exact same things, and it&rsquo;s just hard to tell because of the tiny photo we&rsquo;re looking at.</p>\r\n<p id=\"aSWAPM\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 1.2rem; padding: 0px; color: #424242; background-color: #ffffff;\">It could also be that this is just a different sensor. Huawei, for instance, recently made very good use of a&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; background-color: transparent; color: #e5127d; transition: color 0.1s ease 0s, background-color 0.1s ease 0s, fill 0.1s ease 0s; border-bottom: 1px solid currentcolor;\" href=\"https://www.theverge.com/circuitbreaker/2019/3/26/18282207/huawei-p30-pro-4-camera-array-periscope-zoom-dark-mode\">time-of-flight sensor</a>, which measures distance by tracking how long it takes light to bounce back. On the P30 Pro, it allowed Huawei to create far more realistic portrait mode shots, by more accurately representing the falloff of background blur by using real depth data, instead of interpreting it from the difference between two cameras.</p>\r\n<h3 id=\"jwkMjG\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: Heroic, \'Arial Narrow\', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: calc(1.5625em); line-height: 1.2; margin: 0px 0px 0.6rem; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; text-transform: uppercase; color: #424242; background-color: #ffffff;\">THERE&rsquo;S A DUAL FLASH AND ANOTHER SENSOR IN THE CORNER</h3>\r\n<p id=\"RWIWLM\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 1.2rem; padding: 0px; color: #424242; background-color: #ffffff;\">Like every other Pixel to date, the camera will be accompanied by a dual flash system. You can also see another sensor in the corner (it&rsquo;s just a small dot), though there aren&rsquo;t any obvious clues as to what it&rsquo;ll be. In the past, Google has included an additional microphone, laser autofocus, and a spectral/flicker sensors beside Pixel cameras. The Pixel 3 just includes the spectral sensor, but the only thing we can potentially take off the table here is this being used for laser autofocus, since Google has in the past used two separate sensors to achieve that, while there&rsquo;s only one dot here.</p>\r\n<h3 id=\"v8SqcS\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: Heroic, \'Arial Narrow\', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: calc(1.5625em); line-height: 1.2; margin: 0px 0px 0.6rem; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; text-transform: uppercase; color: #424242; background-color: #ffffff;\">NO REAR FINGERPRINT SENSOR</h3>\r\n<p id=\"lFiOfo\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 1.2rem; padding: 0px; color: #424242; background-color: #ffffff;\">This had been rumored, and now it&rsquo;s official: this&rsquo;ll be the first Pixel to go without a rear fingerprint scanner. What&rsquo;ll Google use instead? Initial speculation was on an in-display fingerprint sensor, since those have been trendy in Android phones this year. But last night,&nbsp;<em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Unbox Therapy</em>&nbsp;suggested Google would instead go with a facial recognition system, like the iPhone X.&nbsp;<em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Unbox Therapy</em>&nbsp;correctly identified that there would be a third sensor above the two cameras, so there&rsquo;s reason to buy into this.</p>\r\n<figure class=\"e-image\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: inherit; margin: 2.2rem 0px; padding: 0px; display: block; color: #424242; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span class=\"e-image__inner\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; display: block; position: relative;\"><span class=\"e-image__image \" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; display: block; width: 739.922px;\" data-original=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/16336582/pixel4.jpg\"><picture class=\"c-picture\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; display: block; width: 739.922px; min-height: 1px;\" data-cid=\"site/picture_element-1560418754_5974_268149\" data-cdata=\"{&quot;asset_id&quot;:16336582,&quot;ratio&quot;:&quot;*&quot;}\"><source style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration: inherit; vertical-align: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\" srcset=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/pWEU25MTE0j8uZqnYDKrZwzQxGc=/0x0:1536x1024/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1536x1024):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/16336582/pixel4.jpg 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/